    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3682.2.3>
    bibo:endPage "269" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "249" ;
    bibo:volume "3682" ;
    dc:creator "Pérez-González, Sergio; Zaballos, Juan P." ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Tarsal tetramery and extreme size reduction in Anillini (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Trechinae): the case of Typhlocharis Dieck, 1869; description of three new species and definition of a new intra-generic species group" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.222603>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.222602>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.222606> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.222603>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Typhlocharis scrofa sp. n. (A, B) Aedeagus: A) median lobe (dorsal view); B) median lobe and parameres (lateral view). C) Female genitalia (ventral view)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/222603/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.222602>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Typhlocharis scrofa sp. n. habitus: ventral (left half: male, right half: female) and dorsal (male) views. Abdomen not shown in dorsal view for a clearer view of elytral apex." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/222602/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.222606>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Different types of gula in the genus Typhlocharis. Light microscopy photographs and schematic diagrams of: A) T. pacensis Zaballos & Jeanne, 1987; wide gula, approx. twice as long as wide, lateral sutures clearly visible. B) T. elenae Serrano & Aguiar, 2002; narrow gula, approx. four of five times as long as wide, lateral sutures clearly visible, subparallel. C) T. scrofa sp. n.; diffuse gula, same proportions as wide gula, but lateral sutures only visible in the proximal and distal ends, partially fused to the cephalic capsule." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/222606/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

